name: Dumpling (3D Printer)
description:
Our 3D printer’s name is Dumpling (aka Hot Dumps)! 

It is a Bambu P1S with optional AMS system. The slicer for it is called BambuStudio, and you can download it yourself, or use BambuStudio on the RadioSnack computers

Specs: 
Build volume : 256mmx25mmx256mm 
Nozzle: 0.4 mm Stainless Steel  

Supported Filaments:  
Ideal: PLA, PETG, TPU, PVA, PET, ABS, ASA 
Capable: PA, PC 

**About Filament: We use PLA filament because it's less stinky than ABS, and in theory more environmentally friendly. The Bambu P1S printer supports other kinds of filament.  If you want to use a different kind of filament, let’s talk about it! Our filament costs about $30 per kilo, or $.03/g.
